## Genome Size
#estimate with checkm2 (stored in gtdb metadata) 
#formula = assembly length / completeness fraction i.e. complete%/100 

```python
df["correct_genome_size"] = df["genome_size"] / (df["checkm2_completeness"]/100) 
```

#Better estimated via micomplete #caution: trained majorly on bacterial genomes
#source: https://github.com/EricHugo/miComplete
